CASE 1
How to search a file based on its name?
 - find /path/ -name <file_name> ( find /home/paul/ -name test)

CASE 2
How to ignore upper & lower case in file name while searching files.
- find /path/ -iname <file_name> 

CASE 3
How to search all the files which start with letter f?
- find /path/ -iname "f*"

CASE 4
How to search all the files with extension .xml or .sh?
- find /path/ -name *.xml -o -name *.sh

-o --> is logical OR operator 
-a --> is logical AND operator

CASE 5
How to find only file or only directory in a given path?
- find /path/ -type f 

- find . -type d ( to find in the present directory)

- f for file
- d for directory
- i for symbolic link
- b for block device 
- s for socket 

CASE 6 
How to search files for a given user only (example: file owned by root user)?
- find /path/ -user root 

- find . -type root (to find in the current location)

CASE 7
How to search a file based on their size?
- find /path/ -size 50M

- find . -size 20M ( for current location) 

- M for MB
- k for KB
- G for GB
- c for bytes 

CASE 8 
How to search all the files whose size are between 10-50 MB? (between range)
- find /path/ -size +10M -size -50M  (+10 more than 10, -50 less than 50)

CASE 9
How to search 15days old files?
- find /path/ -mtime 15

-mtime 15 --> modified exactly 15days ago (between 15 and 16 days ago)
-mtime +15 --> modified more than 15days ago 
-mtime -15 --> modified less than 15days ago (within the last 15 days)


similarly 
 -atime 2: accessed in last two days
 -mmin 10: modified in last 10 min
 -cmin 10: created in last 10 min
 -amin 10: accessed in last 10 min

CASE 10
How to search all the empty files in a given directory?
find /path/ -empty

CASE 11
How to search all the empty files in a given directory and at the same time delete them?
find /path/ -empty -exec rm {} \; - to remove
find . -empty ls -lt {} \; - executes the empty files, then execute the ls -lt

CASE 12
How to search a file based on their permissions?

find /path/ -perm /u=r
find /path/ -perm 777

CASE 13
How to search a file based on the no. of links?
find /path/ -links <no._of_link>

CASE 14
How to search a file based on the inode no.?
find /path/ -inum <inode_no._of_file>

ls -li --> inode number will display

CASE 15
How to search all the files which are modified/created after last.txt file?
find /path/ -newer last.txt

